<li id="cite_note-25"><span class="mw-cite-backlink"><b><a href="#cite_ref-25">^</a></b></span> <span class="reference-text"><i>Fuel Controls Programs</i>:
<ul><li>First enacted: Air Quality Act of 1967, <a href="/wiki/Public_Law_(United_States)" class="mw-redirect" title="Public Law (United States)"><abbr title="Public Law (United States)">Pub. L.</abbr></a><span class="sr-only" style="border: 0;   clip: rect(0, 0, 0, 0); clip-path: polygon(0px 0px, 0px 0px, 0px 0px); height: 1px; margin: -1px; overflow: hidden; padding: 0; position: absolute; width: 1px; white-space: nowrap;">Tooltip Public Law (United States)</span>&#160;<a rel="nofollow" class="external text" href="https://uslaw.link/citation/us-law/public/90/148">90–148</a> § 210.</li>
<li>Location in statute: CAA § 211, <a href="/wiki/Title_42_of_the_United_States_Code" title="Title 42 of the United States Code">42&#160;U.S.C.</a>&#160;<a rel="nofollow" class="external text" href="https://www.law.cornell.edu/uscode/text/42/7545">§&#160;7545</a>.</li>
<li>Major regulations: <span><a href="/wiki/Title_40_of_the_Code_of_Federal_Regulations" title="Title 40 of the Code of Federal Regulations">40&#160;CFR</a> <a rel="nofollow" class="external text" href="https://www.ecfr.gov/current/title-40/part-1090">1090</a></span>.</li></ul>
</span></li>
