<li id="cite_note-44"><span class="mw-cite-backlink"><b><a href="#cite_ref-44">^</a></b></span> <span class="reference-text"><link rel="mw-deduplicated-inline-style" href="mw-data:TemplateStyles:r1215172403"><cite class="citation web cs1"><a rel="nofollow" class="external text" href="https://www.epa.gov/air-quality-implementation-plans/emissions-during-periods-startup-shutdown-malfunction-ssm">"Emissions During Periods of Startup, Shutdown, &amp; Malfunction (SSM)"</a>. <i>Air Quality Implementation Plans</i>. EPA. September 30, 2021. Guidance Memorandum: Withdrawal of the October 9, 2020, Memorandum. <q>EPA is returning to its 2015 policy explaining that State Implementation Plan provisions that provide exemptions from air emissions limits during periods of startup, shutdown and malfunction (SSM) or that provide affirmative defense provisions are not consistent with the Clean Air Act and would not generally be approvable.</q></cite><span title="ctx_ver=Z39.88-2004&amp;rft_val_fmt=info%3Aofi%2Ffmt%3Akev%3Amtx%3Ajournal&amp;rft.genre=unknown&amp;rft.jtitle=Air+Quality+Implementation+Plans&amp;rft.atitle=Emissions+During+Periods+of+Startup%2C+Shutdown%2C+%26+Malfunction+%28SSM%29&amp;rft.date=2021-09-30&amp;rft_id=https%3A%2F%2Fwww.epa.gov%2Fair-quality-implementation-plans%2Femissions-during-periods-startup-shutdown-malfunction-ssm&amp;rfr_id=info%3Asid%2Fen.wikipedia.org%3AClean+Air+Act+%28United+States%29" class="Z3988"></span></span>
